ul.li:
Invoke SeriesSplitter and the subsequent function in separate SQL calls. For example, in this SQL call, company1_stock1_split is the output from SeriesSplitter Example: Partition Splitter:
SELECT * FROM Interpolator ( ON company1_stock1_split AS InputTable PARTITION BY id ORDER BY "period" USING TimeColumn ('period') TimeInterval (86400) InterpolationType ('linear') ValueColumns ('stockprice') Accumulate ('id') DuplicateRowsCount (2) ) AS dt;
The preceding SQL call is likely to perform better than the following call, which uses SeriesSplitter in the ON clause of the subsequent function.
SELECT * FROM Interpolator ( ON ( SELECT * FROM SeriesSplitter ( ON company1_stock1 AS InputTable USING PartitionByColumns ('id') OrderByColumns ('period') SplitCount (50) Accumulate ('stockprice') ReturnStatsTable ('false') ) AS dt1 ) AS input_table PARTITION BY id ORDER BY period USING TimeColumn ('period') TimeInterval (86400) InterpolationType ('linear') ValueColumns ('stockprice') Accumulate ('id') DuplicateRowsCount (2) ) AS dt2;
